## Environment Variables

Configuration options can be set via environment variables by prefixing the option name with `SPEC_KIT_` and converting to uppercase.

For example:
- `spec-kit option-name` â†’ `SPEC_KIT_OPTION_NAME`

## Configuration File

You can also configure Spec-Kit using a configuration file. The default location is `~/.spec-kit/config.toml`.

## Validation

All configuration values are validated against their declared types. Invalid configurations will cause Spec-Kit to fail with a descriptive error message.

